1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:26,120
<i>Let's settle</i>
<i>all debts and their interest today.</i>

2
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,800
If you want to kill me, go ahead.

3
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:31,120
I will take control of all operations.

4
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:36,280
And here is the list
of the employees' new positions.

5
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,320
I think Mr. Na should work in the office.

6
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,880
I want him to learn
from the lower levels up,

7
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:43,200
so people won't gossip

8
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:45,200
that he's soft

9
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,040
and can't even handle low-level jobs.

10
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:16,600
Na, why weren't you answering my calls?

11
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,680
I'm sorry.

12
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:21,000
Mr. Na's unable to talk right now.

13
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,920
Who are you?

14
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,360
Why did you answer a call for him?

15
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,200
I'm a farm worker.

16
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,120
Mr. Na's in a meeting.

17
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,040
My name is Onsa-ang.

18
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,600
I'm Mr. Tatsana's girlfriend.

19
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:32,960
Go tell him

20
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:35,720
that I have a very important matter
to talk to him about.

21
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,000
<i>I'm afraid that's not possible</i>

22
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:39,400
<i>because Mr. Na is negotiating</i>

23
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,360
<i>a 100-million-baht business deal.</i>

24
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,360
<i>If there's anything I can help with,</i>

25
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:44,680
please let me know.

26
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,920
I'm his assistant.

27
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,640
Of course.

28
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,640
I'll tell Mr. Tatsana for you.

29
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:12,240
Right now, the Secretary
and Madam are in deep trouble.

30
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:14,880
If you ask for Mr. Na's help,

31
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,200
- you--
- Jan.

32
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:18,480
Don't bring this up around him,

33
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,000
or I'll be really upset.

34
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:21,320
But Miss,

35
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:22,720
when people love each other,

36
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,320
they would never look down
on their partner.

37
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,280
They would only care about each other.

38
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:30,520
But why do I have to make
Dad's mistake my problem?

39
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,960
Stop talking about this, Jan.

40
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,280
I won't let it stress me out.

41
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,000
Mr. Na.

42
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,720
Where did he go?

43
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,720
Mr. Na?

44
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,520
Mr. Na. Mr. Na.

45
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,960
Uh, are you Ms. Onsa-ang?

46
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:04,520
Oh, I'm from Paisal Farm.

47
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:14,120
Where's Na?

48
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,560
Why didn't he come to pick me up himself?

49
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:19,680
He's still in a meeting,
so he had me come instead.

50
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,960
Please.

51
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,120
Wait.

52
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:30,960
Your hand.

53
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,120
Put them on before touching the luggage.

54
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,320
Then load them into the car.

55
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,840
Roger that.

56
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:44,000
So drivers here dress like this?

57
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,440
How strange.

58
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Hey.

59
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,080
Don't worry about me.

60
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,160
Just go take care of Madam.

61
00:05:57,680 --> 00:06:00,080
Don't let Yai do anything to harm her.

62
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,960
Mr. Yai wouldn't do anything to her.

63
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,320
Listen. If you don't go,

64
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,920
I'll go do it myself.

65
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,880
Yes, Jom?

66
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,600
Yes.

67
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:20,440
Okay.

68
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,240
What did Jom say?

69
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,880
The meeting has ended.

70
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,040
There's nothing wrong.

71
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,520
Please get some rest, Mom.

72
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,840
I'll go out and check.

73
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,400
<i>Watch Mr. Na for me.</i>

74
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,720
<i>I'll hurry there.</i>

75
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,560
Welcome.

76
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:58,280
Please proceed to the main house.

77
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,760
I'll have someone
tell Mr. Na you have arrived.

78
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,560
Oh, Mr. Na's not here.

79
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:03,480
He passed out on the farm.

80
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,440
Pin's taking care of him.

81
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,680
Oh, my.

82
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:07,320
Why did he pass out?

83
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:10,360
Oh, Mr. Na had to oversee
the farm work as well.

84
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:13,600
Noi, lead me to him. Hurry. Oh…

85
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:14,720
Would you like to come with us?

86
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:16,360
Of course.

87
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,240
Did you not hear what she said?

88
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,680
Stop panicking.

89
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:24,000
- Let's go. Now.
- Yes, yes.

90
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:26,360
Please. Please.

91
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:35,040
I'll tell Mr. Yai for you
that you have a sun sensitivity

92
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:37,160
and are allergic to grass and hay.

93
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,000
Don't do that, Pin.

94
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,240
He would get upset

95
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,720
and bully me even more.

96
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,600
Don't you remember that when we were kids,

97
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:51,520
you were always there to save me?

98
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,280
You're…

99
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,560
just as kind as always.

100
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,560
So where is Na right now?

101
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,320
Tell him where to go
if you know where he is.

102
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:15,760
Jom said he's around here.

103
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,320
Miss, are you hurt?

104
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,680
Hey, are you trying to get fired?

105
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,440
Why would you drive like an idiot?

106
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,640
I found Mr. Na.

107
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:45,440
Miss. Miss.

108
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:48,680
Na.

109
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,680
On?

110
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,240
Hey.

111
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,800
Who is this woman, Na?

112
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,520
Tell me right now who she is.

113
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,760
Well, On…

114
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:11,720
Calm down first. Uh…

115
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,360
And…

116
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,800
how did you get here?

117
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,960
Didn't you say
you'd wait for me in Bangkok?

118
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,640
You told me to wait
and didn't go to pick me up

119
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:21,400
because you were busy flirting with her?

120
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,880
How dare you cheat on me…

121
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,520
- …with this country bitch?!
- Wait, On.

122
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,360
- Why would you do this?!
- On, On.

123
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,120
- You're the worst!
- On, calm down.

124
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,760
This is Pinanong, the maid's daughter.

125
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:32,840
Pinanong, the maid's daughter.

126
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,560
Pin who?

127
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:37,640
She's Pin,

128
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,080
the daughter of the maid.

129
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,000
She's been taking care of me
since I was young.

130
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:47,600
Pin?

131
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,280
The naive and dumb young maid

132
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:54,880
you told me about who annoyed you
by following you around?

133
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,600
That's her?

134
00:09:58,640 --> 00:09:59,600
Yes.

135
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:00,960
Well,

136
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,240
I fainted and couldn't get up,

137
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,360
so Pin stayed to watch me.

138
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:08,000
We were waiting for someone
to bring the meds.

139
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:13,880
If you're a maid,
don't act as an equal to the master

140
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,960
or get too close to him.

141
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,280
It's inappropriate.

142
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,200
Na.

143
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,600
I didn't know.

144
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:26,160
I misunderstood.

145
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,560
I'm sorry, darling.

146
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,080
I'm sorry.

147
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:34,680
Are you hurt anywhere?

148
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,280
I feel so bad for Pin.

149
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:43,600
She's heartbroken,
and she got slapped for nothing too.

150
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,680
The wound's still fresh.

151
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:54,560
Good. Rubbing salt in it like this
will teach her a lesson.

152
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,600
Who is wounded?

153
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,320
Mr. Yai.

154
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,240
I misunderstood.

155
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,800
It didn't hurt much, right?

156
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,400
Pin.

157
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,760
Well… I'm okay now.

158
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,000
You can go back to work.

159
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,080
Oh, wait.

160
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:24,000
Jan, give me my bag.

161
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,200
This is for you.

162
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:38,840
Consider it my apology.

163
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:48,920
On.

164
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:50,800
You don't have to.

165
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,400
There's no need
to cling to these things, Na.

166
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:56,080
We bought so many of them in Chinatown

167
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:59,080
to give to maids and workers, right?

168
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:02,640
Have it.

169
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,680
It's my gift to you.

170
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,240
Then,

171
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:20,560
let's get out of here.

172
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,920
I'll introduce you to my aunt.

173
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,240
Alright. Let's go.

174
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:33,280
When a master gives you something,
why don't you bow and say thank you?

175
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,120
Did no one teach you that?

176
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,720
Or did you spend
too much time with animals?

177
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,240
Pin.

178
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:50,800
I didn't mean to bring them here.

179
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:52,960
It was Mr. Yai who ordered me to.

180
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:04,560
Pin. Pin…

181
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,400
Pin asked me to bring the meds for Mr. Na.

182
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,960
Where did they go?

183
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,360
Still hung up on him?

184
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:47,360
Come here.

185
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:55,360
Burn it,

186
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:57,400
so you can finally move on from him.

187
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:09,760
And now,

188
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,720
you can forget about him.

189
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:24,360
<i>Take good care of our Indian cork tree.</i>

190
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:30,760
- Indian cork. Indian cork.
- Pin.

191
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:31,960
- Indian cork tree.
- Pin.

192
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,680
- Are you crazy, Pin?
- Indian cork tree.

193
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,720
Just how cruel do you intend to be?

194
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,440
How could you burn my Indian cork tree?

195
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,680
It hurt you.

196
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:41,760
I burnt it for your sake,
just for you to insult me?

197
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:42,640
That's what I get from doing good?

198
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:43,560
What is this?!

199
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:45,120
I planted it myself.

200
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,240
It's my heart and soul.

201
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:01,440
Back off.

202
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:11,600
Are you happy now?

203
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,720
Huh?

204
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:14,800
Let me see your hand.

205
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:21,640
Did it satisfy you?

206
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,120
So this is

207
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:26,200
what they call

208
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:28,080
"To kick someone
and then give them candy."

209
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:33,520
You intentionally brought that woman
to trample on my feelings.

210
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,120
Are you so satisfied?

211
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,400
Pin.

212
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,240
I never intended to hurt you.

213
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:42,120
Na has a girlfriend.

214
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:44,320
I just wanted to open your eyes.

215
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,840
Is it worth it
to give your life to a selfish man?

216
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:49,000
You don't love anyone,

217
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:52,120
so you only care if it's worth your while.

218
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:54,200
But for me,

219
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:57,000
just being able to love him is enough.

220
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,640
What a stupid theory.

221
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:08,200
We all want to be loved in return, Pin.

222
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:11,960
Don't be so infatuated
that you let him walk all over you.

223
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,920
Have some self-respect.

224
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,240
A woman like me

225
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,240
is already low-born,

226
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:22,360
even without being oppressed.

227
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,400
Come here. Come.

228
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:33,960
The people around him are all weird.

229
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:35,720
They're not all there.

230
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:39,400
I don't believe
he can find someone good to audit us.

231
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,800
It was just a threat.

232
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,680
Oh, Auntie.

233
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,240
Mr. Manager.

234
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:50,080
Are you two being lovey-dovey right here?

235
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:53,200
What about you, Mr. Yai?

236
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,600
I heard there was an all-hands meeting.

237
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,360
I thought it was going to be here.

238
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,440
But surprise, surprise.

239
00:16:57,520 --> 00:17:01,000
You were off doing something
with the maid alone.

240
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,680
Be careful.

241
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:04,400
The workers might lose respect for you,

242
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,079
and it would be hard
for you to control them.

243
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:07,520
Someone gossips about me?

244
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:08,680
I'll cut their tongue.

245
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:11,440
Someone insults me?

246
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,599
I'll slit their throat.

247
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,240
Someone tattles?

248
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:18,200
I'll cut their junk.

249
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,560
That's easy, Auntie.

250
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,160
And from now on,

251
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,640
Pin is no longer your maid.

252
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,800
Because

253
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:34,360
I'm appointing Pin to lead the Accounting
and Finance Department of Paisal Farm.

254
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:36,560
Hey. How could you do that?

255
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:39,280
Pin studied Home Economics,
not Accounting.

256
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:41,040
But even you

257
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:44,720
went to law school
and didn't even graduate.

258
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:47,160
But I can't do it.

259
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:49,680
I'm not good at math

260
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:51,720
and don't know anything about numbers.

261
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:53,480
Please hire an accounting firm.

262
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,720
Why waste money on that?

263
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,280
Our farm has to save money.

264
00:17:58,360 --> 00:18:00,840
- But…
- I agree.

265
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:02,880
Pin has a keen eye for detail.

266
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:06,280
She's the right person for the job.

267
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:07,960
Also,

268
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:11,520
I've always let you
handle my personal finances.

269
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:15,440
Madam.

270
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:18,840
Pin

271
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:22,640
is the one I trust the most.

272
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:26,560
I'll leave it to you.

273
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:34,480
Good.

274
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:37,360
You're no longer a maid.

275
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,400
Take the department head's salary

276
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:41,480
and report only to me.

277
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:44,120
Good.

278
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,280
Krong.

279
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:03,680
I know what you're about to say.

280
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:06,360
Or do you want him
to hire an external auditor?

281
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:09,480
A naive
but straightforward person like her

282
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:10,840
can be dangerous too.

283
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,640
What if she finds something?

284
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:18,400
You seem to know my maid so well.

285
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:24,160
It's not what you think.

286
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:26,680
If she finds the gap,

287
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:29,120
we'll just let her

288
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:31,000
fill in the gap for us.

289
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:42,840
Haven't you tormented me enough already?

290
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:44,400
Idiot.

291
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:45,440
I'm helping you.

292
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:46,760
Are you blind or something?

293
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:49,400
Don't you want to get back
at those people you oppressed you?

294
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,440
I think you just want everyone to think

295
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,480
I'm loyal to you.

296
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:59,160
So, who are you loyal to?

297
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:03,080
I don't need to be loyal to anyone.

298
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,760
I just want to live a peaceful life.

299
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:09,880
If possible,

300
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:13,440
I just want to disappear from this world.

301
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:15,680
What do you mean?

302
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:19,360
You want to kill yourself
because of that unfaithful man?

303
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:22,160
Have you lost your mind?

304
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:24,120
I'm still in my right mind.

305
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,080
I have a mother to take care of.

306
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:39,640
Good.

307
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:42,600
But if you take an easy way out,

308
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:45,400
I'll ask for my money back
from your mother.

309
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:47,120
Don't think you can stiff me.

310
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:49,000
I'll never forget

311
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:51,880
your kindness.

312
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:56,400
I'm going to find a way
to repay all of it.

313
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:58,560
Cool.

314
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:02,800
You must audit the accounts thoroughly.

315
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:06,120
If even a single cent is missing,

316
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,640
all of you must take responsibility.

317
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:10,320
You do know

318
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:12,520
that a fierce guy like me

319
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:14,720
likes to punish hard, right?

320
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,320
Your owner is so dumb.

321
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,520
She's dumb, naive, and stupid.

322
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:41,320
She's just as dumb as you are.

323
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,960
Ugh, so annoying.

324
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:49,600
- Watch out, Yai.
- Whoa, Pan.

325
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:51,440
- Hey.
- Pan, watch out!

326
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:59,360
Come on, buddy. Don't be so petty.

327
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:01,000
I'm not being petty.

328
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:02,040
I'm just mad,

329
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:03,800
because I don't know why I had to get hurt

330
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,560
for a bad friend like you.

331
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:11,360
Because we were born
to be together forever, right?

332
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:14,960
Stop joking.

333
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:17,920
My friend sent me
the name of the audit firm.

334
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,160
Should I make an appointment?

335
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,080
No need.

336
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,480
I already let Pin do it.

337
00:22:22,560 --> 00:22:23,520
What did you say?

338
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,120
Are you crazy?

339
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:28,040
Pin works for Madam Krongsuk.

340
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:30,680
She'd fabricate numbers
if her madam asked her to.

341
00:22:30,760 --> 00:22:32,280
That's want I want to know.

342
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:34,520
I want to test that girl.

343
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:37,200
Yai, from the moment
you set foot in this farm again,

344
00:22:37,280 --> 00:22:39,640
everything has been about Pin.

345
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:41,160
Let me ask you seriously.

346
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:42,520
Did you come back

347
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,840
to take revenge

348
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:45,360
and take back what's yours,

349
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:48,480
or did you come back
just to flirt with Puny Pin?

350
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:57,760
Hey, are you jealous of me?

351
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:58,800
Don't tell me you are.

352
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,800
My heart's fluttering.

353
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,920
Don't play dumb. That's not funny.

354
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:06,360
I risked my life, dodging bullets

355
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:08,560
and beatings to come stay here with you

356
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,880
because my dad told me to protect you,

357
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:14,240
not to come see you
take revenge on that Tsunami

358
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:16,880
for your stupid love triangle game.

359
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:18,280
That's a waste of my time.

360
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:35,520
On.

361
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:39,000
- Hello, Auntie.
- So glad to finally meet you.

362
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:44,560
Na told me so much about you.

363
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:47,560
You're even more beautiful
than I had imagined.

364
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:51,160
You're also different
than what I had imagined.

365
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:54,240
I thought you'd be younger.

366
00:23:57,280 --> 00:24:01,040
Oh, my. Maybe it's time
for a full makeover in Korea.

367
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,640
You must be
the Permanent Secretary's wife.

368
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,400
Hello.

369
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,920
I am Jan,

370
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,400
Miss On's handler.

371
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:13,440
Oh, my.

372
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:15,840
I really can't tell from your aura.

373
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:20,720
So, how long are you planning
to stay here?

374
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:23,480
I'll arrange the cabin
in the resort for you.

375
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,400
I don't want to trouble you with that.

376
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:30,520
You must have booked
a five-star hotel downtown.

377
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:33,280
It's much more convenient that way.

378
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:35,120
I'll stay here.

379
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:37,760
And I'll stay here indefinitely.

380
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:44,320
But I already told On
a lot of people are staying here.

381
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,520
They go in and out freely.

382
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:46,960
We're laid back here.

383
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:49,440
- We don't really have strict orders.
- Yes, yes.

384
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:51,600
It's okay, really.

385
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:54,440
Jan's an expert
when it comes to order and discipline.

386
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:57,080
Jan is my head housekeeper.

387
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,400
She used to supervise maids

388
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,960
and oversee meal preparation
for international guests.

389
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,200
For something this minor,

390
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:03,920
Jan can help with the training.

391
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:08,200
As for me,

392
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:11,000
I will help Na manage this farm myself.

393
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:13,520
Because from what I can see,

394
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,920
this place still needs a major shape-up.

395
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:19,560
Okay.

396
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:21,280
- Right?
- Yes.

397
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:22,600
Let's help each other.

398
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:30,160
What is this?

399
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:32,160
Why is On settling in here?

400
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:33,800
She said

401
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:35,920
she's stressed about her dad's illness,
so she wants to relax.

402
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,720
Then why isn't she staying with her dad?

403
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:39,320
She chose to be with her hubby?

404
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:41,040
I mean with her boyfriend?

405
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:43,760
And did she meet Mr. Yai?

406
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,320
Not yet.

407
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:48,040
He must be busy managing the resort.

408
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:49,600
Good.

409
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:52,520
Give me some time to think
about what we should do.

410
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,040
If the two of them meet,

411
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:55,320
it'll be a mess for us.

412
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,200
Oh, my!

413
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,760
We've seen each other so many times now.
Still shocked every time?

414
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:13,760
Where are you rushing off to?

415
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,520
Ms. On wanted to rearrange Mr. Na's room

416
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:19,520
and told me to throw away all the stuff.

417
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:22,160
So I'm getting the workers to come help.

418
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:24,840
Sorry.

419
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:51,240
These curtains look so dated.

420
00:26:51,760 --> 00:26:53,320
The fabric is also low-quality.

421
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:54,920
They aren't UV-resistant at all.

422
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:58,240
This blanket is clearly
a low-tier knockoff.

423
00:26:58,320 --> 00:26:59,440
Look at this.

424
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:01,400
There are even threads sticking out.

425
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:03,720
And the texture is coarse.

426
00:27:06,560 --> 00:27:07,480
The mattress is stiff too.

427
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:09,440
You wouldn't be able to sleep.

428
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:11,840
And what is this?

429
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:14,080
Look at this, Jan.

430
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:16,760
This lamp is so tasteless.

431
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:18,280
- Ugh.
- Oh, my.

432
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:20,600
How could Na live like this?

433
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:22,600
Miss On.

434
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:27,680
Then, I think we should
go stay in the hotel or resort.

435
00:27:27,760 --> 00:27:29,760
It's inappropriate for you
to stay in the same house

436
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:30,960
as Mr. Tatsana.

437
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:33,640
Don't be too conservative.

438
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:36,640
When we were studying abroad,
we slept in the same room

439
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:37,760
and shared the same place.

440
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:42,520
And don't you tell Mom about this.

441
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:46,080
I don't want her to mention
Dad's debt in Na's presence.

442
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:47,080
I'm ashamed.

443
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:54,920
Noi told me
you wanted to rearrange the room.

444
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:56,320
How may I be of service?

445
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:00,280
Pan, you asshole.

446
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:03,280
There's no way
I'll keep wearing this lame uniform.

447
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:04,240
Just you wait.

448
00:28:04,320 --> 00:28:05,920
I'll get back at you someday.

449
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:12,720
Mr. Yai?

450
00:28:15,080 --> 00:28:16,320
Oh, wait.

451
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,600
I'm sorry.

452
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:19,120
Please forgive me.

453
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:22,480
I forgot to ask
where I should move this to, Miss.

454
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:24,960
Just put it wherever you want.

455
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:26,400
I'll tell Na to buy new ones.

456
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,920
And go remove the curtains too.

457
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,680
I'll change all of them.

458
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:31,720
Hurry and take it away.

459
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:33,240
And the mattress too.

460
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:34,480
Take it out of there.

461
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:36,240
I'll overhaul the whole set.

462
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:39,680
I think this house
needs a lot of renovations.

463
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:46,400
I'll have to find a way
to negotiate with Yai.

464
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:48,400
Auntie!

465
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:49,800
Come with me. Quickly.

466
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:52,560
Nee! Where are your manners?

467
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:54,280
Don't you see I'm talking business?

468
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:56,040
Go save your in-law's life first,

469
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:57,560
and you can talk all you want.

470
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:59,480
On?

471
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:01,200
- Yeah.
- Oh, my.

472
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:05,920
What happened, On?

473
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:09,120
How could you hire
a stupid worker like him?

474
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:11,840
He almost dropped a chair on me and Jan.

475
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:13,240
I'm really sorry.

476
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:15,040
My finger suddenly locked up.

477
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:17,760
Perhaps I've been mowing
the lawn too much lately.

478
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:20,640
Why waste your resources on him?

479
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:22,720
Even trash is more useful.

480
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:26,240
On, if you wanted to move the sofa,

481
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:28,720
why didn't you tell me
to call in the workers?

482
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,880
But he's a worker too.

483
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:32,960
He's the one who picked me up
and brought me here.

484
00:29:33,560 --> 00:29:35,440
You're misunderstanding.

485
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:38,680
- He's not…
- Hey, it's nothing at all.

486
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:43,240
How dare you treat a master like that?

487
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:45,320
What kind of staff training
do they even have here?

488
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:47,840
Whoever hired such crude, untrained trash

489
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:50,400
is a total idiot.

490
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,840
Just fire him.

491
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:55,160
Na.

492
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:56,640
Take On to my room for now.

493
00:29:57,920 --> 00:30:00,800
I said fire him, Auntie!

494
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:04,360
I'm afraid
we can't do that, Sister-in-Law.

495
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:06,920
You're just an employee.

496
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,200
Can't you stay out of this?

497
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:19,000
I'm Tatsana's sister.

498
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:23,520
And this is

499
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:26,440
Mr. Chalit, or Mr. Yai,

500
00:30:26,520 --> 00:30:28,520
the owner of Paisal Farm!

501
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:32,640
- The owner?
- The farm owner?

502
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:34,520
Tatsanee, why did you reveal that?

503
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:38,480
I was having fun with
my beautiful soon-to-be sister-in-law.

504
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:39,440
Oh, man.

505
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:41,360
Well, since we're already here,

506
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:44,280
I'd like to formally
welcome you to Paisal Farm,

507
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:45,880
my beautiful soon-to-be sister-in-law!

508
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:48,720
Let go. Let go of her.

509
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:54,160
But you really have sharp eyes, huh?

510
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:55,120
Look.

511
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:56,800
Look at her hourglass figure.

512
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:59,680
Oh, wow, what a specimen.

513
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:02,120
Come on, come on.

514
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:05,880
I'll appoint you
as head of PR for our resort.

515
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:07,400
Let's look after this place as a team.

516
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:10,520
Wow, a big family full of people
who love each other

517
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:12,880
is pure happiness and warmth!

518
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:16,320
No, Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

519
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,760
What is this madness?

520
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:24,840
Can you tell me what is this madness?

521
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,040
Well,

522
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:40,000
when he was a teenager,

523
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:43,400
Yai assaulted a worker nearly to death,
so he ran away and disappeared.

524
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:45,360
But suddenly, he came back.

525
00:31:45,960 --> 00:31:48,680
I'm gathering evidence
to bring him to justice.

526
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:49,720
Well…

527
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:52,840
I was trying to find
the right time to tell you.

528
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:55,480
But you found out first.

529
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:04,080
I know many of my dad's friends
who are senior police officers.

530
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,440
We can ask them to take him in.

531
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:07,360
I'll call them now.

532
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:09,320
Oh, no. You can't do that.

533
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,360
Don't call them.

534
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:13,520
If word gets out,
Paisal Farm's name will be mud.

535
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:15,600
He's a part of this family anyway.

536
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:19,240
Well, Yai has been cut out of the will.

537
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:21,760
And Mr. Paisal left
the entire farm to Na alone.

538
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:26,320
Then why are you afraid of him?

539
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:27,440
Chase him away.

540
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:31,680
Well, Mr. Yai is Mr. Paisal's son.

541
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:34,160
I want to give him a chance to repent.

542
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:35,600
Yes, yes.

543
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:38,680
And before he passed away,

544
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:41,120
Mr. Paisal left Mr. Yai in my care.

545
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:44,280
I don't want to break
my promise to my benefactor.

546
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:45,880
Please understand me.

547
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:48,480
And what if he does
something disgusting to Miss On again?

548
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:51,640
I think we should go home, Miss.

549
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:52,960
That's good.

550
00:32:53,040 --> 00:32:54,200
No.

551
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:56,080
I'll stay right here.

552
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:58,720
But I'll never consider Yai as family.

553
00:32:59,240 --> 00:33:01,400
And don't ever let him come near me.

554
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,120
Right.

555
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,720
Ugh, it's just one thing after another.

556
00:33:10,800 --> 00:33:13,040
Yai alone already gives me
enough of a headache.

557
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:15,640
And now there's
this elite in-law stirring things up.

558
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:17,000
This is hell.

559
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:18,840
Yeah, this is literal hell.

560
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:22,080
If Pin finds out there's money
missing from the records and tells Yai,

561
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,320
he'd bury us.

562
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:26,600
I won't let him bury us so easily.

563
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:31,240
I'll bury him myself.

564
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:03,080
Pin.

565
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:05,120
Are you awake, Pin?

566
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:11,840
- I'm awake.
- Hey, Pin.

567
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:13,800
What medicine did you give me?

568
00:34:13,880 --> 00:34:16,320
I slept like a log
from yesterday evening until just now.

569
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:18,440
It's the medicine the doctor prescribed.

570
00:34:18,960 --> 00:34:21,679
You were probably too exhausted,

571
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:23,120
so you were out cold.

572
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:24,639
Then I must change my medicine.

573
00:34:25,239 --> 00:34:28,120
I'm a maid.
I can't be sleeping in like this.

574
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,040
And what are you doing?

575
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:33,440
Why aren't you
cooking breakfast for the family?

576
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:34,639
Well,

577
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:36,920
Mr. Yai told me
to audit the farm's financial records.

578
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:40,880
Why would Yai assign tasks to you?

579
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:42,520
Why did you get involved with him again?

580
00:34:43,159 --> 00:34:44,880
I didn't want to.

581
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:47,719
But he's the farm owner,
and he ordered me to do it.

582
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:49,480
How could I refuse?

583
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:50,560
Pin.

584
00:34:50,639 --> 00:34:52,280
You swore with me.

585
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:54,560
Do you want to see me die
the way you swore I would?

586
00:34:55,159 --> 00:34:57,080
But some money is actually missing, Mom.

587
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,080
What did you say?

588
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:02,840
I compared it to my own records.

589
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:06,680
There's even some cash
I collected for Mr. Teera myself,

590
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:08,800
but it hasn't been recorded in the book.

591
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,840
It adds up to millions.

592
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:27,200
Well, well.

593
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:29,360
First day as an office girl.

594
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:31,440
Were you busy
dressing up and putting on makeup?

595
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:33,120
Is that why you're this late?

596
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:34,920
Wow.

597
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:37,640
I think you're the one
who's looking better than usual.

598
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:43,040
Uh… Hey, I…

599
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:45,120
I'm this good-looking every day.

600
00:35:49,120 --> 00:35:50,280
What?

601
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:51,320
It's this late.

602
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:52,760
Why hasn't that slowpoke shown up?

603
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:55,800
She's probably destroying evidence.

604
00:35:56,960 --> 00:35:58,200
Are you that jealous

605
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:00,640
that I'm more interested in Pin than you?

606
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:02,320
Stop with that nonsense.

607
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:04,800
I'm not crazy in love like you are.

608
00:36:07,080 --> 00:36:08,000
Here.

609
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:10,280
I pointed a gun at the Finance staff

610
00:36:10,360 --> 00:36:11,920
and got a backup file.

611
00:36:13,080 --> 00:36:16,120
I'll tell Madam that
Manager Teera's been extorting money.

612
00:36:16,200 --> 00:36:17,720
Mom.

613
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:20,120
You know Madam is a regular
at the gambling den, right?

614
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:25,640
It's just a small amount.

615
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:27,280
There's no way it would be millions.

616
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:30,640
But the den she goes to
belongs to Mr. Tong.

617
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:32,640
When I was locked up there,

618
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:35,600
I overheard that
Madam owes them several million baht.

619
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:38,920
Our farm business is struggling,

620
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:41,760
and they're unable
to pay the workers because of this.

621
00:36:41,840 --> 00:36:43,320
If we let this continue,

622
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:45,560
Paisal Farm will have nothing left.

623
00:36:45,640 --> 00:36:48,240
There is no limit
to what a gambling addict will sacrifice.

624
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:49,760
Yes.

625
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:52,080
Pin is right.

626
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:53,680
I'm terrible.

627
00:36:54,720 --> 00:36:56,840
What I've done is unforgivable.

628
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:58,000
Madam.

629
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:01,280
I've put you both through so much.

630
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:04,240
I've run Paisal Farm into the ground

631
00:37:05,560 --> 00:37:08,480
even though I've tried my best

632
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:11,680
to keep the last property of Mr. Paisal.

633
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:14,240
But now, I give up.

634
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:18,760
Go ahead.

635
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:21,680
Take me to the police.

636
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:24,200
Go ahead…

637
00:37:24,800 --> 00:37:26,040
Madam.

638
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:27,840
Do it…

639
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:31,640
Do it…

640
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:35,760
I give up…

641
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:38,360
PAISAL FARM'S FINANCIAL RECORDS

642
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:39,600
See?

643
00:37:39,680 --> 00:37:42,080
You don't have to be an accountant
to see how messed up this is.

644
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:43,440
More importantly, watch this.

645
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:45,040
Most customer payment receipts

646
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:46,680
have Pin's signature.

647
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:49,120
Some of them were in cash.

648
00:37:49,760 --> 00:37:51,400
But they haven't been deposited
into the account.

649
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:54,800
Pin might be the one who received
the payments and gave them to Madam,

650
00:37:54,880 --> 00:37:55,920
so Pin didn't know where the money went.

651
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:57,680
Fine.

652
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:00,320
Then you wanna bet?

653
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:02,280
If Pin doesn't show up,

654
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:03,240
you'll need to quit stalling

655
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:05,160
and drag all of them to prison.

656
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:07,760
Okay.

657
00:38:07,840 --> 00:38:09,200
Because I'll win for sure.

658
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:18,600
Aunt Un?

659
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:31,680
Oh, Krong?

660
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:33,680
Noi told me you went out early.

661
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,360
I thought something happened.

662
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:36,760
So?

663
00:38:37,360 --> 00:38:38,880
So…

664
00:38:41,120 --> 00:38:43,240
we can enjoy breakfast now.

665
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:52,880
I'm returning the records you gave Pin.

666
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:55,280
And where is Pin?

667
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:56,360
She ran away.

668
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:57,320
Where?

669
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:58,600
I don't know.

670
00:38:58,680 --> 00:38:59,960
So it's clear.

671
00:39:00,040 --> 00:39:01,480
She intended to run.

672
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:05,480
Pinanong was an accomplice
in extorting money from Paisal Farm.

673
00:39:05,560 --> 00:39:06,760
She knew about this.

674
00:39:06,840 --> 00:39:08,520
That's why she wouldn't face you.

675
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:10,440
If you're suspicious of her,

676
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:12,000
just take me instead.

677
00:39:12,080 --> 00:39:13,920
Then you can kill me,

678
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:17,280
torment me, or do anything
people like you are good at.

679
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:25,880
You probably don't know

680
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:30,440
who paid the medical bills
that allow you to run your mouth

681
00:39:30,520 --> 00:39:31,840
in front of me right now.

682
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:34,360
It was Madam.

683
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:36,240
300,000?

684
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:38,080
Where was she supposed to get that money?

685
00:39:38,160 --> 00:39:40,160
Don't you think
it was the money Bandit Yai robbed?

686
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:42,120
I don't believe you.

687
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:44,640
If you give a dog some food,

688
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:47,080
it will still wiggle
its tail with love in front of you.

689
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:50,520
But sacrificing your life
to protect your madam

690
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:52,000
won't give you anything.

691
00:39:52,080 --> 00:39:53,360
But at least

692
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:55,520
I'm grateful for people's kindness.

693
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:57,520
I'm not ungrateful like you.

694
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:03,840
Pin might have gotten away,

695
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:05,800
but don't think you'll walk free.

696
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:07,880
I'll send all of you to prison!

697
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:16,360
Pin extorted the farm's money?

698
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:17,680
That's ridiculous.

699
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:19,720
Yeah, she would never do that.

700
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:22,320
She'd go to the ends of the earth
to return a single baht.

701
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:24,880
True. I agree with you 100%, babe.

702
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:26,280
Pin must have been framed.

703
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:29,560
Un told Mr. Yai herself
that Pin disappeared.

704
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:31,240
If we want to know what's really going on,

705
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:33,360
we must find Pin first.

706
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:36,800
Guys.

707
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:40,000
If you have friends and family anywhere,
spread the word.

708
00:40:40,080 --> 00:40:41,880
Find Pin around this area.

709
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:43,040
Let's help out.

710
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,440
- Yes.
- Mr. Yai…

711
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:48,360
Mr. Yai

712
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:50,040
It must be Mr. Yai.

713
00:40:50,120 --> 00:40:51,960
He's constantly bullying her,

714
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:53,120
so she must not have been able
to take it anymore.

715
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:54,400
Jom.

716
00:40:55,280 --> 00:40:57,520
Stop assuming the worst about Mr. Yai.

717
00:40:57,600 --> 00:40:58,960
It's you

718
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:01,160
who's blindly loyal to Mr. Yai.

719
00:41:02,240 --> 00:41:03,440
I've got an idea.

720
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:04,840
Let's call Ms. Jin.

721
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:07,400
But where's my phone?

722
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:08,640
My phone.

723
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:10,320
It's in your hand, babe.

724
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:11,920
You're all over the place.

725
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:13,480
Such an idiot. That's why I love you.

726
00:41:13,560 --> 00:41:15,640
- What did you say?
- Oh, I love you.

727
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:16,880
Call her now, before it's too late.

728
00:41:24,400 --> 00:41:26,600
Pan, pull over. Pull over. That's Pin.

729
00:41:26,680 --> 00:41:27,960
That's not her.

730
00:41:28,040 --> 00:41:30,560
Do you only see Pin or what?

731
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:37,600
Yes, Dad.

732
00:41:37,680 --> 00:41:38,800
Something bad happened.

733
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:42,400
Hey, stop. Uncle Pload,
I took control of the farm.

734
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:44,360
But the madam is being a bit feisty.

735
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:48,040
Be careful. Don't underestimate her.

736
00:41:48,120 --> 00:41:49,000
<i>Yes.</i>

737
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:50,080
Mr. Yai?

738
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:53,120
I heard Pan. What is wrong with him?

739
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:57,200
He's bloated right now
and farting non-stop.

740
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:59,800
I gotta go, Uncle. It smells so bad here.

741
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:01,120
Let go!

742
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:02,760
Yai.

743
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:05,080
You're trying to keep
something this serious from my dad?

744
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:06,920
Yeah.

745
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:09,040
Don't you tell Uncle Pload
until we find Pin.

746
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:11,840
So annoying.

747
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:15,880
Pload, don't be stressed.

748
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:17,840
No matter what happens, Pan is there.

749
00:42:17,920 --> 00:42:19,280
Mr. Yai will be okay.

750
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,360
Hey.

751
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:23,520
Pan's not that competent.

752
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:25,720
Back in school,

753
00:42:25,800 --> 00:42:28,400
he let Mr. Yai
clash with technical students.

754
00:42:28,480 --> 00:42:30,080
And what did he do?

755
00:42:30,160 --> 00:42:32,560
He ran off somewhere.

756
00:42:32,640 --> 00:42:34,440
You've always been hard on your son.

757
00:42:34,520 --> 00:42:36,040
And look at you.

758
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:38,160
Think about it.

759
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:39,520
When they were young,

760
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:42,960
who was doing
Mr. Yai's homework if not Pan?

761
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:45,400
See? Pan

762
00:42:46,080 --> 00:42:48,200
always has you to back him up.

763
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:50,320
But does Mr. Yai have anyone?

764
00:42:51,240 --> 00:42:52,920
His mom passed away,

765
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:54,840
and his dad was infatuated
with a mistress.

766
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:58,680
I've never forgotten
the look in that boy's eyes

767
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:01,080
the day he fled Paisal Farm.

768
00:43:01,160 --> 00:43:03,960
How could a life fueled by revenge

769
00:43:04,040 --> 00:43:06,560
be a happy life, Pload?

770
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:09,480
It's love

771
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:12,520
that will help heal Mr. Yai's heart.

772
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:15,160
A love like what Mr. Yai's father had?

773
00:43:27,440 --> 00:43:28,280
Hey.

774
00:43:28,360 --> 00:43:29,760
I asked the officer.

775
00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:32,360
They said Jintana's not coming
to the office today.

776
00:43:32,440 --> 00:43:34,360
She has to make her rounds
to vaccinate animals.

777
00:43:34,440 --> 00:43:36,360
But I've got her address.

778
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:38,880
What are you looking for?

779
00:43:39,680 --> 00:43:41,440
Does your car have a charger?

780
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:44,080
My battery died
while I was talking to Win.

781
00:43:44,160 --> 00:43:46,080
I don't know. This is my dad's car.

782
00:43:54,240 --> 00:43:55,680
Yai.

783
00:43:55,760 --> 00:43:58,160
Why are you tearing it? That's my dad's.

784
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:04,640
How many photos have you torn?

785
00:44:04,720 --> 00:44:05,680
You won't forget him anyway.

786
00:44:09,120 --> 00:44:10,320
Forget it.

787
00:44:10,960 --> 00:44:12,040
I'm not judging.

788
00:44:13,240 --> 00:44:14,600
Let's get back to the farm.

789
00:44:14,680 --> 00:44:17,200
Don't you want to go to Jintana's place?

790
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:19,400
Win already sent Jom there,

791
00:44:19,480 --> 00:44:20,920
but no one was home.

792
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:23,240
Then we might have to wait
and interrogate Jintana.

793
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:26,560
She would help her friend.

794
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:29,520
She'd never tell us where Pin went.

795
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:34,120
But I know a better way.

796
00:44:39,880 --> 00:44:41,320
<i>If you want Na back,</i>

797
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:43,600
give me the one who extorted money
by tomorrow before sunset.

798
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:48,160
<i>You're too late, Pinanong.</i>

799
00:44:48,240 --> 00:44:51,440
So I burnt him alive,
taking revenge for you in one go.

800
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:55,240
I never believed you were truly evil,

801
00:44:55,320 --> 00:44:57,280
but now, I'm sure you are.

802
00:44:58,320 --> 00:44:59,560
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't protect you.</i>

803
00:44:59,640 --> 00:45:00,960
I never hated you, Mr. Yai.

804
00:45:44,400 --> 00:45:46,680
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
